# Dual GitHub push

This repo pushes to **two** GitHub remotes via `origin`:

1. https://github.com/osmium0106/manimation.git
2. https://github.com/Osmium-enfec/manimation-enfec.git

When the user asks to push (or commit and push):

1. Never commit or push secrets — confirm `platform/.env` and other ignored files are not staged.
2. Run `git push origin main` (or current branch) — this pushes to **both** URLs configured on `origin`.
3. Do not push to only one remote unless the user explicitly asks for a single target.

Verify remotes: `git remote -v` should show two `(push)` URLs under `origin`.
